title: Volleyball: East Hall gets sweep at Madison County
text:
By AccessWDUN staff Related Articles Volleyball: Gainesville closes out season with sweep of 8- matches Volleyball: Lady Dragons set new wins mark, clinch No. 2 seed in 8-AAA Volleyball: GHS drops pair of matches Volleyball: Gainesville clinches two region wins 
DANIELSVILLE — The East Hall girls volleyball team improved to 32-13 after taking a pair of matches at the Madison County gym. 
The Lady Vikings needed three sets to knock off Madison County 25-16, 11-25, 25-17 and then defeated Hart County 25-10, 25-15. 
For East Hall, Minette Maldonado had 10 points on serve with three aces, 28 kills, and 21 digs and Jessica Chmiel added 11 points on serve with three aces, five kills and six digs. Savannah Thellman had 45 assists and four digs, Lorna Ayon had two kills and 17 digs, and Summer Lindsey had 19 points on serve with 33 digs for the Lady Vikings. 
Niyah Rucker had 11 kills and three blocks, Rachel McGee had 10 points on serve with five kills and four digs, and Holly Poole had 12 points on serve with three kills and 15 digs. 
East Hall will close out its regular season in Region 7-AAA next Thursday against Lumpkin County and West Hall.
